main event: A UFO phenomenon was observed while traveling between Port Lincoln and Melbourne on 28 March 1958.
interesting points: The observation included a radar confirmation of an unusual target,The observation lasted for about 20 seconds,The report suggests the object could be an astronomical or meteorological phenomenon,No further data was available for a conclusive evaluation,The sighting was made by ship crew members.
sighted object: Unidentified flying object indicated by radar blip
witness description: Second Officer, Chief Engineer, Fifth Engineer of the ship
